  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Betmai Hydroelectric Project. Betmai Hydroelectric Project Feasibility Study</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Support the creation, improvement and sustainability of physical infrastructure, and related services, in both urban and rural areas, to enhance the economic environment and improve economic productivity, including for women. The main infrastructures include energy, including electric power transmission lines and distribution networks, oil/gas terminals, refineries, storage facilities and pipelines; telecom and ICT; and transport, including roads, airports, railways, and ports.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This award supports the creation, improvement and sustainability of physical infrastructure, and related services, in both urban and rural areas, to enhance the economic environment and improve economic productivity, including for women,. More specifically, this award includes a A USTDA grant to the Sewa Energy Resources Ltd. of Sierra Leone will fund a feasibility study to determine the viability of a 27 megawatt run-of-river hydropower project at Betmai Falls on the Pampana River. The Study is expected to have positive developmental, social, and economic impacts in Sierra Leone, and create an opportunity for U.S. companies to provide goods, services, and expertise to the development of the Sierra Leone energy market.. A USTDA grant to the Sewa Energy Resources (SL) Ltd. of Sierra Leone will fund a feasibility study to determine the viability of a 27 megawatt run-of-river hydropower project at Betmai Falls on the Pampana River. The Study is expected to have positive developmental, social, and economic impacts in Sierra Leone, and create an opportunity for U.S. companies to provide goods, services, and expertise to the development of the Sierra Leone energy market. The Grantee has selected Knight Piesold and Co. of Denver, Colorado to perform the feasibility study.. Betmai Hydroelectric Project Feasibility Study.</narrative>
  </description>
